      "writtenOn": "2020-04-16T23:36:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve looked through the rest and I think the semantic API  you want to provide is:\n\nPermExists(perm) bool\nQueryAuthorized(real, perm) bool\n\nSo, I find it unfortunate that PermissionIndex has to be exposed. My alternative is to keep 2-level map and \"suffer\" a string hash lookup in PermExists and QueryAuthorized:\n\ntype Reams struct {\n  names \u003d ..\n  realms \u003d map[string]map[string]groupsAndIdents  // perm -\u003e realm -\u003e who has it\n}\n\n\nHowever, I realize that this is *internal* implementation of server/auth, so its API isn\u0027t really important, so i guess ignore my ramblings.",
      "parentUuid": "a72382d9_880eef4e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 39,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 39,
        "endChar": 72
      },
      "revId": "964cb6dd0cd9ed1fb6f422d2dff3cb21b3ae403e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
